Construct Red Team Operation Plan in Markdown
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Design and document a comprehensive Red Team operation plan using Markdown format
Create visual threat heatmaps using Python and Matplotlib to identify high-risk areas
Generate professional Red Team engagement reports with actionable recommendations
Apply threat modeling techniques to create realistic attack scenarios
Document findings and methodologies in a format suitable for stakeholder presentation
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic understanding of cybersecurity concepts and the MITRE ATT&CK framework
Familiarity with Linux command line operations and text editors
Basic knowledge of Python programming and data visualization concepts
Lab Environment
Your cloud machine comes pre-configured with:

Python 3.8+ with pip package manager
Text editors (nano, vim)
All necessary Python libraries (matplotlib, numpy, pandas, seaborn)
Simply click Start Lab to access your dedicated environment.

