Troubleshooting Tips
Issue 1: Python Libraries Not Installing
Symptom: pip install fails or libraries not found

Solution:

pip3 install --user matplotlib numpy pandas seaborn
# Or use system package manager
sudo apt-get install python3-matplotlib python3-numpy python3-pandas python3-seaborn
Issue 2: Matplotlib Display Errors
Symptom: "no display name and no $DISPLAY environment variable"

Solution: Add this to the top of your Python scripts:

import matplotlib
matplotlib.use('Agg')  # Use non-interactive backend
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
Issue 3: Permission Denied When Saving Files
Symptom: Cannot write to output directories

Solution:

chmod -R 755 ~/redteam-lab3
# Ensure directories exist
mkdir -p ~/redteam-lab3/{assets,reports}
